ysical and policy-driven containment has shaped the lives of the urban poor, while wealth and access to resources have been historically concentrated in elevated areas—truly “the heights.” Moga’s innovative framework expands our understanding of how planning and economic segregation alike have molded the American city.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCity planningxHealth aspectszUnited States. 0aCity planningzUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aCity planningzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aDiscriminationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aNeighborhood planningzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aNeighborhood planningzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zUnited States. 0aUrban healthzUnited States. 0aUrban minoritieszUnited States. 0aUrban poorzUnited States. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  acity planning.  adisease fears.  aneighborhood.  apoverty.  aslum.  aurban landscape.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226710679423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226710679.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  UChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020